HEADWORD: Wrinkly
<hw>Wrin"kly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Full of wrinkles;
having a tendency to be wrinkled; corrugated; puckered.</def> <rj><au>G.
Eliot.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His old <qex>wrinkly</qex> face grew quite blown out at last.</q>
<rj><qau>Carlyle.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wrist</ent>⟦br⟧
